-- Johnson Electric Eyes Serbia Site for Supplying European Clients
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-11-20T11:30:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-20/johnson-electric-eyes-serbia-site-for-supplying-european-clients.html
Johnson Electric Holdings Ltd. (179)  which
makes electric motors for the  auto industry  and consumer goods,
may open a plant in northwestern Serbia for supplying European
clients.  The facility, near the city of  Sombor  and close to the
border with Hungary and Croatia, would employ as many as 2,000
with output intended mainly for Germany and Hungary, Sinisa
Lazic, the head of the local municipal assembly, said in a phone
interview following talks with Johnson Electric officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
